body.name: MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi Computer Gaming Motherboard (AM5, ATX, DDR5, PCIe 4.0, M.2, SATA 6Gb/s, USB 3.2 Gen 2, HDMI/DP, Wi-Fi 6E, AMD Ryzen 7000 Series Processors) AMD PC Motherboards (Renewed)
features: Future-Ready Performance: The MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi Gaming Motherboard is designed to support the upcoming AMD Ryzen 7000 Series Desktop Processors, ensuring exceptional performance for gaming, content creation, and more.
DDR5 and PCIe 4.0: Embrace the latest in memory and data transfer technology with support for DDR5 memory modules and PCIe 4.0, allowing for lightning-fast data speeds and potential GPU advancements.

Storage Versatility: With multiple M.2 slots and SATA 6Gb/s ports, this motherboard offers ample storage options, from high-speed NVMe SSDs to traditional storage devices, catering to a wide range of storage needs.

Immersive Connectivity: Featuring HDMI and DisplayPort outputs, the motherboard enables multi-monitor setups with 4K resolution support, enhancing your visual experience for gaming, productivity, and entertainment.

Advanced Wireless and Networking: Experience low-latency online gaming and high-speed data transfers with integrated Wi-Fi 6E technology, making it perfect for competitive gamers and those who demand reliable wireless performance.
body.description: The MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi Gaming Motherboard is a cutting-edge motherboard designed to elevate your gaming experience to new heights. Engineered to support the latest technologies, this ATX motherboard is a perfect match for the AMD AM5 socket and the future-ready DDR5 memory standard. With its PCIe 4.0 support, the motherboard enables lightning-fast data transfer speeds and the potential for future graphics card advancements. Equipped with multiple M.2 slots, the motherboard boasts impressive storage capabilities, enabling you to harness the power of high-speed NVMe SSDs. The SATA 6Gb/s ports provide ample connectivity for traditional storage devices as well. The inclusion of USB 3.2 Gen 2 ports ensures rapid data transfers and seamless connectivity for a wide range of peripherals. Gamers and content creators will appreciate the motherboard's comprehensive display options, including HDMI and DisplayPort, allowing for multi-monitor setups and 4K resolution support. The integrated Wi-Fi 6E technology ensures low-latency online gaming and high-speed data transfers, making it an ideal choice for competitive gamers and those who demand the best wireless performance. Designed to accommodate the upcoming AMD Ryzen 7000 Series Desktop Processors, the MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi Gaming Motherboard provides a solid foundation for your next-generation computing rig. Its robust power delivery system, advanced cooling solutions, and optimized circuit layout ensure stable performance even under demanding workloads.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for My Ryzen 7900X and G.Skill TridentZ Combo!
reviews.reviewText: I've recently given my gaming rig a boost with the renewed MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi motherboard, and it's an ideal match for my AMD Ryzen 7900X CPU and 32GB of G.Skill TridentZ RAM.Switching to DDR5 and PCIe 4.0 with this motherboard has been a game-changer. Together with the Ryzen 7900X and high-speed RAM, it's like a turbo boost for gaming and multitasking. My games run smoother than ever, and tasks are completed in a flash.The compatibility with AMD Ryzen 7000 Series Processors is fantastic. This motherboard handles the 7900X like a pro, delivering top-notch system performance. The Wi-Fi 6E feature is a real bonus for online gaming, keeping the connection fast and stable, even during intense multiplayer sessions.The generous connectivity options, including USB 3.2 Gen 2, HDMI/DP, and M.2 support, mean I'm never short on ports for my gadgets. And the support for multiple M.2 SSDs means I can keep all my games and files without a hitch.Opting for a renewed unit was a smart budget move, and it performs just as well as a brand-new motherboard. MSI's quality and reliability shine through.The MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WiFi has truly amped up my gaming experience with my Ryzen 7900X and G.Skill TridentZ setup. If you're looking to jump on the DDR5 and PCIe 4.0 bandwagon with an AMD Ryzen 7000 Series CPU, this motherboard is an excellent choice. It's given my setup a much-needed boost, and I couldn't be happier with it. Top marks all around!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Supposedly it was tested it fully working
reviews.reviewText: Product arrived in original box in an ESD bag with all the necessary parts. Upon inspection I found a couple of pins that were bent and what appeared to be debris in the socket. So, I benchtested it myself. It powered up fine with 32gb ram installed in the A2/B2 slots and I got a 3 long beep RAM POST error. Took out the A2 slot RAM and it loaded to BIOS. Swapped out DIMMS in the B2 to check to see of a DIMM was bad. Restarted and it loaded to BIOS. Put the 2nd DIMM back in the A2 and got the POST error. Bent pins correlate to the memory slot, so I'm returning it for a refund. Buyer beware when it reads that it was fully tested, because if this was fully tested, they need new testers.
